Interface TilUtlaan


  • public interface TilUtlaan
    Classes which implements this interface will be able to set Strings out for loan. An already loaned string can't be loaned out twice. It can also return the loaned items back.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean objectIn(String id)
      method objectIn takes one parameter, this String parameter is the name of the object which will be returned again.
      boolean objectOut(String id)
      method objectOut takes one parameter, this String parameter is the name of the object which will be loaned out.

    • Method Detail

      • objectOut

        boolean objectOut(String id)
        method objectOut takes one parameter, this String parameter is the name of the object which will be loaned out. An already loaned out string can't be loaned out again. If the method successfully loaned out an object, it will return true, if not false will be returned
        Parameters:
        id - String which will be loaned out
        Returns:
        True/false depends if the object is loaned out or not.

      • objectIn

        boolean objectIn(String id)
        method objectIn takes one parameter, this String parameter is the name of the object which will be returned again. If the String was not loaned out beforehand, it will return false. But if the object is successfully returned, true will be returned.
        Parameters:
        id - String which will be returned
        Returns:
        True/false depends if the object already is loaned out or not.
